Package: marcher
Type: Package
Title: Migration and Range-Change Estimation in R
Version: 0.0-2
Authors@R: c(person("Eliezer", "Gurarie", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "egurarie@umd.edu"), person("Farid", "Cheraghi", role = "aut"))
Description: A set of tools for likelihood estimation and model selection for various 
  two- and three-range shift models for animal movement data is built into this package. The method is described 
  in detail in: E.Gurarie, F. Cagnacci, C. Fleming, W. Peters, J.M. Calabrese, T. Muller and W. Fagan.  
 A framework for modeling range shifts and migrations: Asking whether, whither, when, and will it return, Journal of Animal Ecology. It's pronounced "marshay!".
License: GPL-2
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.0)
Imports:
    stats,
    Matrix,
    graphics,
    grDevices,
    plyr,
    mvtnorm,
    RColorBrewer,
    minpack.lm,
    zoo,
    numDeriv,
    magrittr,
    scales
VignetteBuilder: knitr
